It is difficult to tell whether the Dead believe themselves to be dead, or to be sleeping.
As they never sleep, they use the same word for both.
Regardless, they believe that when they die in this world, they will awaken into their true life.

The Dead King is married to the Living Queen. He brings the night.
Since they cannot leave their separate realms until the world ends, he seeks to end the world.
The god of life feries mortals back to the land of the living at the end of their sleep.
The navigator paddles the world through the oceans of the universe.
Nightmare is responsible for all the pain suffered in this sleep.
